<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="359" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="359">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="359">
The placement of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Setalidius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Setalidius griseolum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="griseolum">Setalidius griseolum</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Sphodrosomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphodrosomus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sphodrosomus</taxonomicName>
is primarily supported by shared features of the male genitalia and female reproductive tract (Figs 38-39, 41-42). The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Wagler, 1830" authorityName="Wagler" authorityYear="1830" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Homalosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Homalosoma" order="Squamata" pageId="22" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Homalosoma</taxonomicName>
is part of the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trichosternus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trichosternus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Trichosternus</taxonomicName>
series of 
<bibRefCitation author="Moore, BP" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="26" pageNumber="363" pagination="1 - 32" title="Studies on Australian Carabidae (coleoptera) 4. - The Pterostichinae." url="doi: 10.1111/j.1365-2311.1965.tb00042.x" volume="117" year="1965">Moore (1965)</bibRefCitation>
and those taxa have a distinct set of characteristics that have not been found in any New Caledonian carabids.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
